<section class="hero" style="padding-bottom: 2rem;">
    <div class="hero-glow"></div>
    <h1>Why Melodic?</h1>
    <p class="hero-sub">
        A PHP framework that values clarity, explicit code, and developer understanding.
    </p>
</section>

<section class="features-section">
    <h2 class="section-heading">Built on principles, not conventions</h2>
    <p class="section-sub">Three ideas that shape every decision in the framework.</p>
    <div class="features" style="grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);">
        <div class="feature-card">
            <h3>Explicit over Implicit</h3>
            <p>No facades, no magic methods, no service locators. Every dependency is visible in the constructor. Every data access path is traceable through Query and Command objects.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature-card">
            <h3>Composition over Inheritance</h3>
            <p>Middleware pipeline for cross-cutting concerns. Service providers for modular registration. No deep inheritance chains or abstract layers to navigate.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature-card">
            <h3>Simplicity over Features</h3>
            <p>Minimal API surface. The framework does a few things well rather than everything poorly. No built-in ORM, no template syntax to learn, no convention-heavy scaffolding.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

